<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Early_life">Early life</span></h2>

<p>Nadella was born into a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telugu_people" title="Telugu people">Telugu</a>-speaking
    family<sup id="cite_ref-sg_10-0" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-sg-10">[10]</a></sup> in <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyderabad" title="Hyderabad">Hyderabad</a>, <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telangana" title="Telangana">Telangana</a>, <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India" title="India">India</a>. His father, Bukkapuram Nadella
    Yugandher, was a civil servant of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Administrative_Service"
                                             title="Indian Administrative Service">Indian Administrative
        Service</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-dnaindia_11-0" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-dnaindia-11">[11]</a></sup><sup
            id="cite_ref-Satya_Nadella_Eenadu_12-0" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-Satya_Nadella_Eenadu-12">[12]</a></sup> Nadella
    attended the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyderabad_Public_School#Notable_alumni"
                    title="Hyderabad Public School">Hyderabad Public School, Begumpet</a><sup id="cite_ref-13"
                                                                                              class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup> before attaining a bachelor's
    degree in electrical engineering<sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup> from the <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manipal_Institute_of_Technology"
            title="Manipal Institute of Technology">Manipal Institute of Technology</a> in 1988 (then affiliated with <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mangalore_University" title="Mangalore University">Mangalore
        University</a>), <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manipal" title="Manipal">Manipal</a>, <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karnataka" title="Karnataka">Karnataka</a>.<sup
            id="cite_ref-Official_Bio_15-0" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-Official_Bio-15">[15]</a></sup><sup
            id="cite_ref-16" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-16">[16]</a></sup></p>

<p>Nadella subsequently traveled to the U.S. to study for an M.S. degree in <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_science" title="Computer science">computer science</a> at the
    <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Wisconsin%E2%80%93Milwaukee"
            title="University of Wisconsin–Milwaukee">University of Wisconsin–Milwaukee</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-17"
                                                                                                 class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-17">[17]</a></sup> receiving his degree in 1990.<sup
            id="cite_ref-18" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-18">[18]</a></sup> Later he received an MBA from the
    <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Chicago" title="University of Chicago">University of
        Chicago</a> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Booth_School_of_Business" title="Booth School of Business">Booth
        School of Business</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Time_19-0" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-Time-19">[19]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-20"
                                                             class="reference"><a
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/#cite_note-20">[20]</a></sup></p>

<p>Nadella said he "always wanted to build things".<sup id="cite_ref-21" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-21">[21]</a></sup> He knew that computer science was
    what he wanted to pursue,<sup id="cite_ref-22" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-22">[22]</a></sup> but that passion was at
    precocious stage while studying at Manipal University. "And so it [electrical engineering] was a great way for me to
    go discover what turned out to become a passion," he says.<sup id="cite_ref-msftceo_23-0" class="reference"><a
                href="#cite_note-msftceo-23">[23]</a></sup></p>